...this is unique. In the middle of this section is this room - a very lively place compared to the coldness of everywhere else. For one, it has... actual sunlight? That's right, the ceiling extends quite high (even a ladder wouldn't reach it), revealing glass panes (good luck breaking them, they won't) that let the sun (or moon) light come in. It always seems to be a bit cloudy up there, but otherwise there's nothing to note and nothing major to see. The rest of this room is pretty nice, too. There are plenty of newly-made wooden benches on the rim of this place, but in the middle lies a field of artificial grass and a whole playground, like the one you would see at parks. A perfect place to play some games to pass the time... if you were small children. The air here also just... feels fresher. You're not sure if it's artificially being freshened up or being taken from actual nature itself, but the air in this room feels nice. In fact, this room even has a 'breeze' flow through it at times, blurring the line between the outside and here. (edited)
